"use strict";

module.exports = {
  slug:  "notifications",
  title: "Notifications",
  body: [
  '<h1>Notifications</h1>',
  '<p><code>b.notify</code> is the generic dispatcher for any channel an app might send to: log, Slack, custom HTTP webhook, push, SMS. <code>b.events</code> is the framework-internal event bus that primitives use to surface lifecycle events for the operator to subscribe to.</p>',

  '<h2 id="notify">b.notify <a class="anchor" href="#notify">#</a></h2>',
  '<p>A channel entry is either a <em>Transport</em> directly (<code>{ name, send }</code>) or a config wrapper (<code>{ transport, retry?, breaker?, timeoutMs?, serialize? }</code>). The dispatcher owns retry, circuit breaking, timeout, redaction, and audit around the transport\'s <code>send</code>.</p>',
  '<h3>b.notify.create(opts)</h3>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">{',
  '  channels:          { [name]: Transport | ChannelConfig },',
  '                                            // required: true',
  '  audit:             AuditTap,              // default: null',
  '  auditSuccess:      boolean,               // default: true',
  '  auditFailures:     boolean,               // default: true',
  '  redact:            (value) =&gt; value,      // default: b.redact.redact',
  '  defaultTimeoutMs:  number,                // default: C.TIME.seconds(30)',
  '  defaultRetry:      RetryOpts,             // default: b.retry.DEFAULT_RETRY',
  '  defaultBreaker:    BreakerOpts,           // default: null — opt-in per channel',
  '  queue:             QueueInstance,         // default: null — async dispatch backing',
  '  clock:             () =&gt; number,          // default: Date.now',
  '}',
  '',
  '// Transport contract:',
  '{',
  '  name:    string,',
  '  send:    async (message, sendOpts) =&gt; { id?, status, attempts?, durationMs? },',
  '}',
  '',
  '// ChannelConfig wrapping a transport with per-channel overrides:',
  '{',
  '  transport:  Transport,                    // required: true',
  '  retry:      RetryOpts,                    // default: defaultRetry',
  '  breaker:    BreakerOpts,                  // default: defaultBreaker',
  '  timeoutMs:  number,                       // default: defaultTimeoutMs',
  '  serialize:  boolean,                      // default: false — Mutex around send',
  '}</code></pre>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">var notify = b.notify.create({',
  '  channels: {',
  '    log:    b.notify.transports.log(),',
  '    slack:  b.notify.transports.httpJson({',
  '      url:   env("SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL"),',
  '      shape: function (msg) { return { text: msg.text }; },',
  '    }),',
  '    sms:    {',
  '      transport: operatorTwilioShim,             // operator-supplied { name, send }',
  '      retry:     { maxAttempts: 3 },             // per-channel override',
  '      breaker:   { failureThreshold: 5, cooldownMs: C.TIME.seconds(30) },',
  '      timeoutMs: C.TIME.seconds(10),',
  '    },',
  '  },',
  '  audit: b.audit,',
  '});',
  '',
  'await notify.send({',
  '  channel: "slack",',
  '  message: { text: "Deploy started by " + actor.email, password: "leaked-here" },',
  '});',
  '// Slack receives { text: "Deploy started by alice@..." }; the audit row',
  '// records the metadata with `password` redacted via b.redact.redact.</code></pre>',
  '<p>Three transports ship in the box under <code>b.notify.transports</code>: <code>log()</code> (writes via <code>b.log</code>), <code>httpJson({url, shape?})</code> (POSTs JSON to a URL), and <code>test()</code> (capture for tests). Slack, email, SMS, push — all are operator-supplied <code>{ name, send }</code>. Failures route through <code>b.retry</code> + <code>b.retry.CircuitBreaker</code>; broken channels emit <code>notify.send.failure</code> on the audit chain plus an observability counter so ops dashboards see the outage.</p>',

  '<h2 id="events">b.events <a class="anchor" href="#events">#</a></h2>',
  '<p>The framework-internal event bus. Primitives publish lifecycle events here so operators can subscribe without having to wrap the primitive in their own EventEmitter. Events are typed; the published list of names lives at <code>b.events.EVENTS</code> so editor autocomplete catches typos.</p>',
  '<pre><code class="language-javascript">b.events.on(b.events.EVENTS.API_ENCRYPT_FAILURE, function (info) {',
  '  // { reason, ip, path, method, ts, requestId }',
  '  myDashboard.recordApiEncryptFailure(info);',
  '});',
  '',
  'b.events.on(b.events.EVENTS.CLUSTER_LEASE_RELEASED, function (info) {',
  '  // { fencingToken, releasedBy }',
  '  myAlerter.alert("cluster leadership changed");',
  '});</code></pre>',
  '<p>The bus is best-effort: a listener that throws is caught + logged but doesn\'t affect the publishing primitive. Use it for ops-dashboard wiring and incident-response automation; for state-mutating reactions, the <a href="/observability#audit">audit chain</a> is the right primitive.</p>',
].join("\n"),
};
